German Prosecutors Chase Tax Evaders in Luxembourg, FTD Reports

-- B y   J a n a   R a n d o w
-- 
2011-10-14T06:32:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/german-prosecutors-chase-tax-evaders-in-luxembourg-ftd-reports.html
German prosecutors are preparing to
chase tax evaders with bank accounts in Luxembourg,  Financial
Times Deutschland  reported.  National authorities, together with those in  Germany ’s most
populous state of North Rhine-Westphalia, purchased a CD
containing data from 3000 customers of the Luxembourg branch of
 HSBC Holdings Plc. (HSBA) , the newspaper said. Germany’s finance
ministry confirmed the information, according to the newspaper.
The CD cost 3 million euros ($4.1 million), FTD added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
